I don&#39;t think it excludes using it as a location device, however. The  
issue is the audience, not the location. If you&#39;re on location,  
personally experimenting, it seems to function just fine in many cases.

The issue here is not taking a chance in front of an audience. I feel  
more than a bit conflicted about what the answer to that properly is.

Ann

